title: WEDNESDAY - Questions surrounding Super Wildcard Weekend 2021
itunes:title: WEDNESDAY - Questions surrounding Super Wildcard Weekend 2021
description:
The Texans finally get their man to help lead the organization (0:06). The Browns get some bad news (0:40) ahead of their first playoff game since 2002, and the Seahawks could be without a key piece of their defense (1:15). Washington quarterback Alex Smith (1:32) still dealing with a calf injury that could create a unique situation for their playoff game against the Buccaneers. Colts QB Philip Rivers (3:06) talks about what a Super Bowl title would mean to him, and the 15 Semifinalists for the Pro Football Hall of Fame are announced
